WORLD; 
E. EUROPEAN FUTURE ON AGENDA 
Czechoslovakia, Hungary and Poland took the first steps today toward creating 
new working relationships to replace the Warsaw Pact and its economic trading 
arm, Comecon, and speed integration with the rest of Europe. 
Ministers from the three states -- plus those from the observer nations of 
Austria, Yugoslavia and Italy -- formed positions on economic cooperation that 
took into account the diminishing military threat in Central Europe, Hungarian 
acting President Matyas Szuros said. 
